# Vibecoding Protocol

Windsurf must use repository files as the source of truth.

Startup:
- Read `docs/AI_STATE.yml`.
- Read `docs/VIBECODING_WORKFLOW.md`.
- Read `docs/AI_RULES_INDEX.md`.
- Read `docs/ai/PLAN_PROTOCOL.md`.
- Read the current task card.
- Read related specs, designs, and plans.
- Run `bash scripts/ai-preflight.sh T-xxx`.

Shared prompt modules:
- `prompts/00-agent-contract.md`
- `prompts/01-explore-readonly.md`
- `prompts/02-plan-locked-task.md`
- `prompts/03-implement-current-step.md`
- `prompts/04-command-classifier.md`
- `prompts/06-closeout-report.md`

Planning:
- Windsurf plans are scratch work.
- Write the final plan and allowed file scope into repository task and plan
  files.

Completion:
- Run `bash scripts/drift-guard.sh`.
- Run `bash scripts/task-closeout.sh T-xxx --write-report`.
- Report commit and push checkpoints.
